com.samysadi.acs.utility.factory.generation.mode

Class AbstractGenerationMode

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.samysadi.acs.utility.factory.generation.mode.AbstractGenerationMode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    GenerationMode, Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FrequencyGenerationMode, RandomGenerationMode

    public abstract class AbstractGenerationMode
extends Object
implements GenerationMode
    Abstract GenerationMode where possible configurations are determined as follows.

    It is assumed that all configuration candidates are put under the same configuration.
    Each candidate's context contains two String parts. A fixed prefix which is the same between all other candidates. And, an integer suffix that distinguish it between other candidates.
    For example, multiple host configurations maybe named: Host0, Host1, Host2 ...

    When instantiating this class, all configuration candidates are determined and put under a list which is accessible by subclasses using the protected configurations field.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Samy Sadi , Belabbas Yagoubi
